e>99%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Если допустить, что начальный %ib%i восходит здесь к %iv%i (как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærgæ"/>), то можно возводить к <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>vaid-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w>vid-</w> <gloss><q>знать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/> <gloss><q>замечать</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр. в каузативном значении: ‘делать заметным’. %n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JRAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр. 33</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p. 33</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">If the initial %ib%i is assumed to be traced back to %iv%i (like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærgæ"/>), then the word can be traced back to <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>vaid-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w>vid-</w> <gloss><q>know</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/> <gloss><q>notice</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc. in the causative meaning: ‘make noticable’. %n<bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JRAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр. 33</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p. 33</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>